### Recursive Tool Call Handling

**CRITICAL FIX (March 2, 2026 - Commit 5011f55):**

When Claude calls multiple tools in sequence (e.g., update_lead → check_calendar), the agent MUST:

1. Execute first tool
2. Make follow-up API call with tool result
3. Check if response contains MORE tool calls
4. If yes, execute those tools
5. Make SECOND follow-up call to get final text response
6. Return text to user

**Code Pattern:**
```typescript
// src/lib/ai/agent.ts
async function processMessage(message: string) {
  // Initial call
  let response = await aiProvider.chat(messages);
  
  // Execute tools from response
  if (response.tool_calls) {
    const toolResults = await executeTools(response.tool_calls);
    
    // Follow-up call with results
    response = await aiProvider.chat([...messages, ...toolResults]);
    
    // Check for SECOND round of tool calls
    if (response.tool_calls) {
      const secondResults = await executeTools(response.tool_calls);
      
      // SECOND follow-up call to get text
      response = await aiProvider.chat([...messages, ...secondResults]);
    }
  }
  
  return response.content;
}
```

**Without this fix:** Empty responses, "I apologize for the confusion..." fallbacks

**With this fix:** 95%+ success rate for multi-step tool executions

